I'm concerned that the size of the company might be a sticking point:  though there are certainly more than 15 employees in the office, he has it structured so that there are five or six different companies, and different employees technically work for different &quot;companies.&quot;  Would he be able to claim exemption based on that fact, or would the fact that he owns all the companies and runs them out of the same office come into play?<br>
